# Racing by Design

## Introduction @showdialog
### @preferredEditor asset

**Here's a game where you race a peach down the track and try to avoid hurdles and branches.**

Soon, you‚Äôll be able to customize this game for yourself! You can design your own
background scene, main character, and hurdles!

What and how will you be racing today?

![Peachtree game in simulator](/static/skillmap/peachtree/peach1.gif "Animated peach with black sunglasses on track")


## {Step 2 - Play the OG}


**Play the game**

- :circle play: Press play on the game window to see the project in action.

üí° _Use the (A) button (or space bar) to help your peach jump and avoid the hurdles._

---

- :mouse pointer: When you're ready for a new step, click **NEXT**
to start making your own art.



## {Step 3 - Open the Background image}


**üè° Set the scene üè°**

- :binoculars: Start by finding the image called **background**.

- :paint brush: Click on the background image and select **Edit**
beneath the
**Asset Preview** pane to open the image editor.

- :mouse pointer: Once the image editor opens, click **NEXT**
to get to the next instruction.


## {Step 4 - Edit the Background}

**Create your own background image**<br/>
üé® üé® üé®

- :paint brush: Use the pencil tool on the left to edit the background,
or use the eraser to clear the image and start over.

- :mouse pointer: Once you're happy with your new background, click **Done** to save it and return
to the **My Assets** window.

---

üí° _You can also select the transparent swatch (the grey & white checkered square)
to erase parts of the image using any of the paint tools._

![UseImageEditor](/static/tutorials/image-editor.gif "This is how you use the image editor)



## {Step 5 - Try the Game}

**Take a look at the game simulator** <br/>
üïπÔ∏è üïπÔ∏è üïπÔ∏è

 How does your background look?

 If you want to make more changes, you can edit the background as many times
 as you need to!

 - :mouse pointer: Click **NEXT**
to edit your racer.



## {Step 6 - Design the Hero Character}

**Now let's edit our hero** <br/>
üòé üòé üòé

Who do you want the hero to be in your race?

- :mouse pointer: Click on the image called **peach** and choose
**Edit** from below the **Asset Preview** pane.

- :paint brush: Change the peach in any way you want or delete it altogether
and draw something
new.

- :mouse pointer: When you're happy, click **Done** to go back
to the **My Assets** window.


## {Step 7 - Play Again}

**Play your game again.**

 Try your game again with your new hero.  How do you like it? <br/>
 Does anything else need to change?


## {Step 8 - Draw a Collectible Object}

**Edit it all!**

- :mouse pointer: Follow the same steps to edit any or all of the other images!

- :mouse pointer: When you're finished, play your game again, then click **Done** to share your game and
open the finished product in the project editor where you can see the code that created it!
